    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-10-20T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-10-20T18:00:00-05:00" n="11"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d11">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.61/289a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJC2" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-10-20T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 20, 1933—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>99. For your information, the President made public this afternoon an exchange of
                    messages between himself and the President of the All Union Executive Committee,
                    Moscow, in consequence of which it is to be expected that the Russian Government
                    will send to Washington <persName>Litvinoff</persName>, Commissar for Foreign
                    Affairs, to discuss questions outstanding between the two countries. In
                    commenting briefly to press correspondents upon this action, the President
                    explained that this step does not constitute recognition.</p>
                <p>Text is being sent by naval radio to Peiping for relay to you.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
